narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you are a painting concentration, definitely take this class as soon as you can, you learn a lot about yourself and what matters to you.
Best painting class I have taken at Yale. if you're an Art (Painting concentration) major, you'll likely take this no matter who is teaching it, but if it's Clint, you're in for a treat.

If the class was at a different time, it would be absolutely great. It gives you a good amount of freedom, but keeps you on track so that you're actually going in some sort of direction. Sometimes it's a bit hard to figure out what you're trying to accomplish in the class, but that is more of a personal situation, generally. The largest considerations regarding taking the class would be would the schedule work for you, and can you handle the expense of what is needed for a painting studio course?
